Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{1%drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Preheat the #grill{} to high.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, pepper chunks and corn. Stir-fry until golden, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%min} more.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}. Taste and season with salt and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce (in whichever pan is biggest). Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar. Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and golden, ~{7-8%mins}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your bowls. Enjoy!